FBIS4-61032 "drsov085_b_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-085 Daily Report 2 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Approves Initiative on Reinforcing Statehood Yeltsin Approves Initiative on Reinforcing Statehood LD0205115894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 2 May 94 LD0205115894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Russian BFN [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin has approved an initiative by Russian legal scholars on conducting research into ways and means of strengthenening Russian statehood. The head of state's press service reports that the president also confirmed by edict the main areas of this research which primarily concerns the formulation of legal enactments that have to be in line with the constitution. One of the primary tasks envisioned is the drafting of laws on the government and on federal ministries. Scholars also believe that legal enactments relating to the observance and protection of human rights and freedoms need to be brought into line with generally accepted principles and standards of international law.
